caption: Table 8: Sizes of the two employer datasets to be matched.

Table 9: Running time for blocking and matching with Ditto. Ad-

vanced blocking consists of two steps: computing the representa-
tion of each record with Sentence-BERT [43] (Encoding) and sim-
ilarity search by blocked matrix multiplication [1] (Search). With 
advanced blocking, we only match each record with the top-10 most 
similar records according to the model.
Table 10: Baseline results from different sources.

Table 11: The average prediction time (ms) per data entry pair of 

Ditto.

Table 12: The F1 scores of the baseline method with different pre-

trained LMs. The first 4 columns are performance of the baseline 
Ditto using the 4 different LMs. We highlight the LM of the best 
performance on each dataset, which form the baseline column in

Table 5. We turned on the summarization (SU) optimization for the 
Company dataset to get F1 scores closer to the full Ditto.
